Wollongong City Council

Public Transport

Wollongong’s public transport network includes buses and Sydney Trains.

Buses and trains across Wollongong accept Opal Cards. To find out more or get an Opal Card, visit the Opal website.

Visit the Transport for NSW website to plan your journey by bus or train.

There are also some great mobile apps to help you get around on public transport.

Wollongong is part of the Sydney Trains network. Trains are a great way to get around locally, or between Wollongong and Sydney, including Sydney airport.

For more information, visit the Sydney Trains website.

Gong Shuttle

The free Gong Shuttle Bus (55A and 55C) links the centre of Wollongong with the railway station, the hospital, TAFE and University campuses, and beaches.

The Gong Shuttle runs every 10 to 20 minutes.

Other buses

You can find information about local bus routes on the Transport for NSW website.

Parking Services

There are numerous services available at Vienna International Airport for vehicles parked there to make your stay at the airport as pleasant as possible.

Services rund ums Parken

Relax – we clean & park

We will look after your vehicle while you are away. Park your car and let us wash it in your absence. On your return, your car will be waiting for you spick and span.

The check-in carwash on level 2 in multi-story car park 4 is a new first-class service. It is designed to suit customer needs, with computerised process control that represents a new dimension in car cleaning.

The installation uses steam cleaning appliances, one of the most up-to-date and resource-sparing methods available. On request, cleaning agents can be used for upholstery, mats, carpets and wheel rims that will not only spruce up their appearance but also help them to last longer.

Make a reservation and enjoy the benefit of a vehicle cleaned thoroughly and flawlessly by hand.


Tel: +43-1-7007-35462

Charging stations for electric vehicles can be found at Vienna International Airport on level 0 in multi-story car park 4 and next to open-air car park C.

Electric vehicles with type 2 or CHAdeMO standard can be quickly recharged. In car park C there are also charging stations for electric bikes and scooters, ideal for cyclists using the airport cycling path.

All that is required is a TANKE card. Instructions can be found on all TANKE charging stations.

P0089 Engine Fault Code

Check Solution For P0089 OBD Code :

P0089 engine code seems a kind of powertrain problem, we try to show one by one the meaning and the solution.
Brief explanation of the P0089 code and definition of P0089 is the bottom side.

P0089 Meaning :

p Powertrain Code
Problem is related engine, transmission and emissions systems.
0 SAE - Generic
0 Fuel And Air Metering
8 Exhaust Gas Recirculation System Valve 1
9 Kick-Down Switch Failed Short

SAE - Generic codes, which have a '0' as their second digit to indicate they are common to all makes and models of vehicles. These are the codes that are required for basic emissions fault diagnosis.

How To Fix P0089 ?

Deactivation of cylinders is achieved by releasing a synchroniser pin that normally interlocks the cam follower and rocker arms. P0089 code resolves the synchroniser pin is released using hydraulic pressure which is controlled by a dedicated solenoid.

P0089 Code Description:

Is the fuel pump sometimes not priming when you turn the key to ON(II)? Start by measuring the fuel pressure and checking whether you have bright white-bluish spark at all four plugs. The mechanical timing is also something that you should check, as we mentioned above. When you see P0089 engine fault code on your engine code reader this description will help you.

Shipping Information

Unlike many other web sites that have special rules and lots of fine print, Kawachigroup has a transparent and clear shipping policy for all orders placed on our website, without any special exceptions.

Just because shipping is free doesn't mean it should take a long time. Kawachigroup understands that getting your items quickly is important to you, so we make every effort to process your order quickly.

We are committed to delivering your order accurately, in good condition, and always on time promised by us in our website.

  • We offer some article FREE Shipping (specified on the Product detail page) on selected products ordered through
  • Each order may be shipped only to a single destination address specified at the time of payment for that order. If you wish to ship products to different addresses, you shall need to place multiple orders.
  • We make our best efforts to ship each item in your order within 2-3 working days of the order. However in some cases, we may take longer, up to 5 working days, to ship the order as we may have to procure it from some other stores or our suppliers.
  • We ship on all week days (Monday to Saturday), excluding public holidays.
  • To ensure that your order reaches you in the fastest time and in good condition, we only ship through reputed courier agencies.
  • While we shall strive to ship all items in your order together, this may not always be possible due to product characteristics, or availability.
  • If you believe that the product is not in good condition, or if the packaging is tampered with or damaged, before accepting delivery of the goods, please refuse to take delivery of the package, and call our Customer Care 09326110110 or log on to, mentioning your order reference number. We shall make our best efforts to ensure that a replacement delivery is made to you at the earliest
  • You may track the shipping status of your order on our website, by clicking at Track your Order section.

Please note all items (including gifts) will be shipped with an invoice mentioning the price, as per Indian Tax Regulations.
